~let() function

A ~let() function that display text using various FIGlet ASCII Art fonts. Includes 34 fonts.

Author: Trispis@M*U*S*H, Sketch@M*U*S*H, Javelin@M*U*S*H
Category: Fonts
Commands: @create, @lock, @parent, @set.
Functions: after(), ansi(), before(), chr(), edit(), filter(), first(), fold(), foreach(), hasattrp(), if(), ifelse(), index(), lattrp(), localize(), map(), mix(), nor(), not(), num(), ord(), regeditall(), regmatch(), rest(), rjust(), setinter(), setq(), setr(), switch(), t(), tagwrap(), trim(), u(), v(), words().
Features: %:.
Compatibility: CobraMUSH, PennMUSH.

Instructions

Copy and paste the below code into a compatible MUSH or MUX.

MUSHCode for ~let() function

Select Code

@@ ~let()
@@ ~let(<font[:<ansi>]>,<string>)
@@
@@ with no arguments returns the #dbref of the ~let function object, followed by a list of all installed fonts.
@@
@@ if <font> (optional :<ansi>) and <string> are provided, it returns one of the following...
@@
@@ #-1 if <font> does not exist.
@@ #-2 if there are characters in <string> which aren't supported in <font>
@@ or, <string> in <font> with optional <ansi> applied.

@@ Font Library 1, 2 and 3 are included, and contain the following fonts:
@@ BASIC BIG BIGCHIEF DIGITAL DOH DOOM GOTHIC GRAFFITI INVITA ISOMETRIC ISOMETRICSM JERUSALEM LARRY3D MIRROR
@@ POISON ROMAN RUE BROADWAY BROADWAY_KB CYBERMEDIUM DRPEPPER EFTICHESS EFTIWALL FIRE_FONT-K GRACEFUL HIEROGLYPHS
@@ LILDEVIL PEPPER RECTANGLES SLANT SMALL SMSHADOW SPEED DANC4

@create Font Library 3
@lock Font Library 3==me
@set Font Library 3 = VISUAL
@set Font Library 3 = HALT
@set Font Library 3 = NO_COMMAND

&FONT`DANC4`CRED`ORIG Font Library 3=
&FONT`DANC4`CRED`ORIG`0 Font Library 3=flf2a$ 4 4 48 0 20 0 0
&FONT`DANC4`CRED`ORIG`1 Font Library 3=DANC4 by Richard Sabey <cryptic_fan@hotmail.com> 9.2003
&FONT`DANC4`CRED`ORIG`10 Font Library 3=should type only the letters, and uppercase the *last* letter of every word
&FONT`DANC4`CRED`ORIG`11 Font Library 3=except the last. For example "Come, Elsie!" becomes comEelsie.
&FONT`DANC4`CRED`ORIG`12 Font Library 3=The messages in dancing-men cipher in DANC didn't use the letters
&FONT`DANC4`CRED`ORIG`13 Font Library 3=FJKQUWXZ. What's more, editions of DANC vary in what mistakes they make in
&FONT`DANC4`CRED`ORIG`14 Font Library 3=the cipher, though they are consistent in using the same figure for P & V.
&FONT`DANC4`CRED`ORIG`15 Font Library 3=To resolve this problem and supply the missing figures, I follow the TrueType
&FONT`DANC4`CRED`ORIG`16 Font Library 3=font designed in 1994 by Martin Bergman of Sweden.
&FONT`DANC4`CRED`ORIG`17 Font Library 3=The positions of the flags have been altered to keep this a 4-line FIGfont.
&FONT`DANC4`CRED`ORIG`18 Font Library 3=
&FONT`DANC4`CRED`ORIG`19 Font Library 3=
&FONT`DANC4`CRED`ORIG`2 Font Library 3=This font is based on the "dancing men" cipher used in Sir Arthur Conan
&FONT`DANC4`CRED`ORIG`20 Font Library 3=
&FONT`DANC4`CRED`ORIG`3 Font Library 3=Doyle's Sherlock Holmes story "The Adventure of the Dancing Men" (DANC),
&FONT`DANC4`CRED`ORIG`4 Font Library 3=which was later published in the collection "The Return of Sherlock Holmes".
&FONT`DANC4`CRED`ORIG`5 Font Library 3=The cipher ignores punctuation, and marks a space by a flag held by the
&FONT`DANC4`CRED`ORIG`6 Font Library 3=dancing man for the last letter before the space. The last figure of
&FONT`DANC4`CRED`ORIG`7 Font Library 3=an entire message carries no flag, as there is no need for one. In this
&FONT`DANC4`CRED`ORIG`8 Font Library 3=implementation of the cipher, figures with no flags represent lowercase
&FONT`DANC4`CRED`ORIG`9 Font Library 3=letters; those with flags, uppercase letters. Thus, when FIGletising, you
&FONT`DANC4`CRED`PENN Font Library 3=
&FONT`DANC4`CRED`PENN`00 Font Library 3=Conversion to ~pig() format by Chuc McGuire, aka 'tramp'.
&FONT`DANC4`CRED`PENN`01 Font Library 3=Conversion via flf2msh.pl, by Alan Schwartz

&FONT`GRACEFUL`CRED`ORIG`3 Font Library 2=Why did I make this font? Most of the figlet fonts are ugly for my taste.
&FONT`GRACEFUL`CRED`ORIG`4 Font Library 2=Chars ".", "'" or "|" are not as graceful as "(", ")", "/", "\" and "_".
&FONT`GRACEFUL`CRED`ORIG`5 Font Library 2=Also most of the fonts unlike this one are either small or good, not both.
&FONT`GRACEFUL`CRED`ORIG`6 Font Library 2=And finally, I wanted to have a strictly sized font, this one is 6x4.
&FONT`GRACEFUL`CRED`ORIG`7 Font Library 2=I intended to create this elegant figlet font in 1996, but only in
&FONT`GRACEFUL`CRED`ORIG`8 Font Library 2=January 2002 actually had the time to bring it to the working state. :)
&FONT`GRACEFUL`CRED`ORIG`9 Font Library 2=Cyrillic letters are supported, maybe somewhen I will add hebrew latters.
